asset_dbtable_set¶

Accessor to the related objects manager on the reverse side of a many-to-one relation.

In the example:

class Child(Model):
    parent = ForeignKey(Parent, related_name='children')

Parent.children is a ReverseManyToOneDescriptor instance.

Most of the implementation is delegated to a dynamically defined manager class built by create_forward_many_to_many_manager() defined below.

class Forms.models.FormResponse(*args, **kwargs)¶

Bases: Model

A FormResponse is a model that represents a user’s response to a form.

Parameters:

  • form_id (models.ForeignKey) – The form that the response is associated with.

  • response (models.JSONField) – The user’s response to the form in JSON format.

  • created_at (models.DateTimeField) – The date and time the response was created.

  • updated_at (models.DateTimeField) – The date and time the response was last updated.

  • content_type (models.ForeignKey) – The type of content in the response.

  • object_id (models.PositiveIntegerField) – The ID of the related object.

  • Instancia (GenericForeignKey) – The instance of the related object.

Returns:

The name of the form associated with the response.

str

Instancia¶

Provide a generic many-to-one relation through the content_type and object_id fields.

This class also doubles as an accessor to the related object (similar to ForwardManyToOneDescriptor) by adding itself as a model attribute.
